shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_0"><![endif]>To
change the attributes of an asteroid simply double-click it. This will disp=
lay
an editing panel at the right of the screen.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Here you can change the asteroids name or alter its si=
ze.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>The image used to display the asteroid can be changed =
by
clicking the arrows in the horizontal scroll bar underneath the first image.
The landscape image used to show the ground-level view of the asteroid can =
be
changed by clicking the arrows in the horizontal scroll bar underneath the
second image.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>You may also apply any scenery or research bonuses.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Resources can be added or removed from the asteroid.
Quantity and abundance levels for resources can be changed. Click in the
&#8220;Qty&#8221; or &#8220;%&#8221; columns of the resources grid to change
these values.</p>

